Niheer Dasandi

University of Birmingham
n.dasandi@bham.ac.uk

Abstract

We look at the link between public health issues and climate change discussed in the UN General Debates.

  • Pre-processing
  • Analysis 25 words

Loading data from the UNGDC data

#Loading packages and data
library(readtext)
library(quanteda)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(stringr)
library(ggplot2)
library(rworldmap)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(haven)
library(readxl)
DATA_DIR <- "~/Dropbox/Research/UN Data/" 
ungd_files <- readtext(paste0(DATA_DIR, "Converted sessions/*"), 
                                 docvarsfrom = "filenames", 
                                 dvsep="_", 
                                 docvarnames = c("Country", "Session", "Year"))
#changing the names of documents to remove file pathways from readtext
ungd_files$doc_id <- str_replace(str_replace(sapply(str_split(ungd_files$doc_id, "/"),`[`,2), ".txt", ""), "_\\d{2}", "")
#creating corpus object from text
ungd_corpus <- corpus(ungd_files, text_field = "text") 
ungdc.2017 <- corpus_subset(ungd_corpus, Year==2017)
ungdc.lancet <- corpus_subset(ungd_corpus, Year>2006)
corp_summary <- summarise(group_by(summary(ungd_corpus, n = 7897),Year),
                           n(),sum(Sentences),sum(Tokens))
readr::write_csv(corp_summary, "corp_summary.csv")

Tokenizing corpus.

#Tokenization and basic pre-processing
tok <- tokens(ungd_corpus, what = "word",
              remove_punct = TRUE,
              remove_symbols = TRUE,
              remove_numbers = TRUE,
              remove_twitter = TRUE,
              remove_url = TRUE,
              remove_hyphens = TRUE,
              verbose = TRUE)

tok.m <- tokens_select(tok, c("[\\d-]", "[[:punct:]]", "^.{1,2}$"), 
                       selection = "remove",

tok.r <- tokens_tolower(tok.m)

Analysis 25 words

Stage 1 - Public Health terms

Creating compound tokens from the key terms identified by experts:

mylist <- list( c("malaria"), c("diarrhoea"), c("infection"), c("disease"), c("sars"), c("measles"), c("pneumonia"), c("epidemic"), c("pandemic"), c("public", "health") , c("health","care"), c("epidemiology"), c("healthcare"), c("health"), c("mortality"), c("morbidity"), c("nutrition"), c("illness"), c("infectious"), c("ncd"), c("non-communicable", "disease"), c("noncommunicable","disease"), c("communicable", "disease"), c("air", "pollution"), c("nutrition"), c("malnutrition"), c("mental", "disorder"), c("stunting"), c("climate","change"), c("global","warming"), c("green","house"), c("temperature"), c("extreme","weather"), c("global", "environmental", "change"), c("climate","variability"), c("greenhouse"), c("low","carbon"), c("ghge"), c("renewable","energy"), c("carbon","emission"), c("co2","emission"), c("climate","pollutant")) 
 
tok.compound <- tokens_compound(tok.r, mylist, valuetype = "fixed", concatenator = "_")

Creating the dictionary object of climate change terms identified by experts:

climate_dict <- dictionary(list(climate =  c("climate_change", "global_warming", "green_house", "temperature", "extreme_weather", "global_environmental_change", "climate_variability", "greenhouse", "low_carbon", "ghge", "renewable_energy", "carbon_emission", "co2_emission", "climate_pollutant")))
health_dict <- dictionary(list(health = c("malaria", "diarrhoea", "infection", "disease", "sars", "measles", "pneumonia", "epidemic", "pandemic", "public_health", "health_care", "epidemiology", "healthcare", "health", "mortality", "morbidity", "nutrition", "illness", "infectious", "ncd", "non-communicable_disease", "noncommunicable_disease", "communicable_disease", "air_pollution", "nutrition", "malnutrition", "mental_disorder", "stunting")))

Look up health and climate term counts

total_dfm <- dfm(tok.compound)
health_dfm <- dfm_lookup(total_dfm, health_dict, valuetype = "fixed")
climate_dfm <- dfm_lookup(total_dfm, climate_dict, valuetype = "fixed")
#creating a data frame 
health <- as.data.frame(health_dfm)
climate <- as.data.frame(climate_dfm)
PHCC_counts <- left_join(health, climate, by = "document")
#converting documentID into two columns - country and year
PHCC_counts <- PHCC_counts %>%
  separate(document, c("country", "year"), "_")
#year as numeric
PHCC_counts$year <- as.numeric(PHCC_counts$year)
PHCC_counts <- plyr::rename(PHCC_counts, c("health"="PH", "climate"="CC"))
readr::write_csv(PHCC_counts, "PHCC_counts_fixed.csv")

Intersection

Performing a key-word-in-context search for public health key terms. The window is set to 25 words before and after the term - reflecting approximately half a paragraph before and after the term (on average a paragraph in English is 50 words). UNGD speeches are highly structured documents drafted over long periods of time and reflect internal discussions and negotiations in government.

tok.hea <- kwic(tok.compound, c("malaria", "diarrhoea", "infection", "disease", "sars", "measles", "pneumonia", "epidemic", "pandemic", "public_health", "health_care", "epidemiology", "healthcare", "health", "mortality", "morbidity", "nutrition", "illness", "infectious", "ncd", "non-communicable_disease", "noncommunicable_disease", "communicable_disease", "air_pollution", "nutrition", "malnutrition", "mental_disorder", "stunting"), window = 25, valuetype = "fixed")
readr::write_csv(tok.hea, "health_kwic_25_fixed.csv")
tok.cc <- kwic(tok.compound, c("climate_change", "global_warming", "green_house", "temperature", "extreme_weather", "global_environmental_change", "climate_variability", "greenhouse", "low_carbon", "ghge", "renewable_energy", "carbon_emission", "co2_emission", "climate_pollutant"), window = 25, valuetype = "fixed")
readr::write_csv(tok.cc, "climate_kwic_25_fixed.csv")

Text surrounding health terms (half a paragraph context) are saved and transformed to a corpus object and tokenised for second stage analysis. Tokens are next converted to a document-feature matrix (DFM) for analysis.

corpus_health <- corpus(tok.hea, split_context = FALSE)
tok.health <- tokens(corpus_health, verbose = TRUE)

Finished tokenizing and cleaning 8,478 texts.
health_tok_dfm <- dfm(tok.health)
#document names to reflect ISO code and Year. KWIC transformation above replaced docids.
docvars(health_tok_dfm, "docid") <- str_sub(health_tok_dfm@Dimnames$docs, start=1, end=8)
#grouping DFM by country-year, so that there's one row per country-year
health_dfm <- dfm_group(health_tok_dfm, groups = "docid")

Stage 2 - Mentions of climate change in public health context

Looking up and counting terms from climate change dictionary in the health DFM:

x_dfm <- dfm_lookup(health_dfm, climate_dict, valuetype = "fixed")
#creating a data frame 
intersection <- as.data.frame(x_dfm)
#converting documentID into two columns - country and year
intersection <- intersection %>%
  separate(document, c("country", "year"), "_")
#year as numeric
intersection$year <- as.numeric(intersection$year)
#keeping only country-years with at least one mention of CC in PH conext
mentions <- subset(intersection, climate!=0)
readr::write_csv(mentions, "mentions_25_fixed.csv")

Total counts by WHO region

Using UN M49 Standard (Standard country or area codes for statistical use (M49)) we create regional and sub-regional groupings of countries. [https://unstats.un.org/unsd/methodology/m49/]

#loading WHO regions country identifiers and preprocessing
regions <- read.csv("UNSD - Methodology.csv")
regions$ISO.alpha3.Code <- as.character(regions$ISO.alpha3.Code)
regions$Region.Name <- as.character(regions$Region.Name)
regions$Sub.region.Name <- as.character(regions$Sub.region.Name)
regions$WHO <- as.character(regions$WHO)
#UNGDC used YUG designation while WHO is using SRB
intersection$country <- str_replace(intersection$country, "YUG", "SRB")
PHCC_counts$country <- str_replace(PHCC_counts$country, "YUG", "SRB")
#merging WHO designations with mention counts
regional_data <- inner_join(PHCC_counts, regions, by = c("country" = "ISO.alpha3.Code"))
regional_data <- left_join(regional_data, intersection, by = c("country", "year"))
#replacing NAs with zeros
regional_data["climate"][is.na(regional_data["climate"])] <- 0
# total sum of mention counts by year and WHO region, with means
reg_sum <- summarise(group_by(regional_data, year, WHO), 
                     count = sum(climate), mean = mean(climate),
                     count_PH = sum(PH), mean_PH = mean(PH),
                     count_CC = sum(CC), mean_CC = mean(CC))

Proportion of countries plots

Proportion of countries that had at least one mention

Proportion for all countries

Data preparation

#number of countries with a mention (any number)
mentions_annual <- summarise(group_by(mentions, year), numerator = n())
mentions_annual_CC <- summarise(group_by(mentions_CC, year), numerator_CC = n())
mentions_annual_PH <- summarise(group_by(mentions_PH, year), numerator_PH = n())
#total number of countries delivering a speech at UNGD per year
all_annual <- summarise(group_by(ungd_files, Year), denominator = n())
#merging numerator and denominator
all_speeches <- left_join(all_annual, mentions_annual_CC, by = c("Year"="year"))
all_speeches <- left_join(all_speeches, mentions_annual_PH, by = c("Year"="year"))
all_speeches <- left_join(all_speeches, mentions_annual, by = c("Year"="year"))
#replacing NAs with zeros
all_speeches["numerator"][is.na(all_speeches["numerator"])] <- 0
all_speeches["numerator_CC"][is.na(all_speeches["numerator_CC"])] <- 0
all_speeches["numerator_PH"][is.na(all_speeches["numerator_PH"])] <- 0
# percentage of countries per year with at least one mention of CC in PH context
all_speeches$percent <- all_speeches$numerator/all_speeches$denominator*100
all_speeches$percent_CC <- all_speeches$numerator_CC/all_speeches$denominator*100
all_speeches$percent_PH <- all_speeches$numerator_PH/all_speeches$denominator*100

Proportion by WHO region

Data preparation

mentions.regional <- subset(regional_data, climate!=0)
#number of countries with at least one mention by WHO region and year
mentions_climate_regional <- summarise(group_by(mentions.regional, year, WHO), numerator = n())
PH.regional <- subset(regional_data, PH!=0)
#number of countries with at least one mention by WHO region and year
mentions_PH_regional <- summarise(group_by(PH.regional, year, WHO), numerator_PH = n())
CC.regional <- subset(regional_data, CC!=0)
#number of countries with at least one mention by WHO region and year
mentions_CC_regional <- summarise(group_by(CC.regional, year, WHO), numerator_CC = n())
ungd_files$Country <- str_replace(ungd_files$Country, "YUG", "SRB")
# getting WHO region designations to all countries who gave a speech in UNGD
all_regional <- inner_join(ungd_files, regions, by = c("Country" = "ISO.alpha3.Code"))
# calculating total number of countries by year and WHO region who gave a speech in UNGD
all_reg_annual <- summarise(group_by(all_regional, Year, WHO), denominator = n())
# merging numerator and denominator
all_reginal_speeches <- left_join(all_reg_annual, mentions_PH_regional, by = c("Year"="year", "WHO"))
all_reginal_speeches <- left_join(all_reginal_speeches, mentions_CC_regional, by = c("Year"="year", "WHO"))
all_reginal_speeches <- left_join(all_reginal_speeches, mentions_climate_regional, by = c("Year"="year", "WHO"))
# replacing NAs with 0s
all_reginal_speeches["numerator"][is.na(all_reginal_speeches["numerator"])] <- 0
all_reginal_speeches["numerator_PH"][is.na(all_reginal_speeches["numerator_PH"])] <- 0
all_reginal_speeches["numerator_CC"][is.na(all_reginal_speeches["numerator_CC"])] <- 0
# calculating the percentage of countries with any mention of CC in PH context by WHO region and year
all_reginal_speeches$percent <- all_reginal_speeches$numerator/all_reginal_speeches$denominator*100
all_reginal_speeches$percent_PH <- all_reginal_speeches$numerator_PH/all_reginal_speeches$denominator*100
all_reginal_speeches$percent_CC <- all_reginal_speeches$numerator_CC/all_reginal_speeches$denominator*100
